            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> But I'm not sure how this could be upstreamed without the rest of Treesitter Text Objects.\n\nThat. We are not looking to maintaining more treesitter queries (with the possible exception of indents, but these cannot be upstreamed as-is). If(!) such mapping overrides were added, they would have to rely on the standard highlight queries.\n\n(Alternatively, adding such motions to nvim-treesitter-textobjects could be in scope, but right now that plugin does not set up _any_ mappings for you.)",
