        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> If(!) such mapping overrides were added, they would have to rely on the standard highlight queries.\n\nThat would be fine, even if not 100% accurate or precise, anything would be an improvement over the existing builtin `[m` & co. capabilities.\n\n`:h treesitter-highlight-groups` already lists `@function` / `@function.method` as standard highlight groups, which I assume are backed by equivalent queries. Maybe these could serve as the basis for the new mappings?",
